1. A method of manufacturing a printed circuit board, comprising:
providing a substrate including a first circuit layer having a lower land of a via;
forming an insulating layer on the first circuit layer;
forming a via hole in the insulating layer so that the lower land is exposed;
filling the via hole with a first metal, thus forming a via;
forming a seed layer with a second metal on the insulating layer and the exposed surface of the via;
applying a resist film on the seed layer, and then forming a resist pattern having an opening for a second circuit layer, a width of the opening formed on the via being smaller than a width of the via;
plating a circuit region defined by the opening with a third metal, thus forming a plating layer formed of the third metal; and
removing the resist film, and then selectively removing an exposed portion of the seed layer, thus forming a second circuit layer.

